{"title": "Teacher-Parent Romance", "content": "\"Tell me, how does my mother, or any person for that matter, go into a parent/teacher conference and come out with a date?\"\n\nIn fiction, this is commonly one of the worst nightmares for students: their bachelor/bachelorette parent dating one of their teachers. Even worse, their teacher becoming their step-parent. Even if the teacher is a Cool Teacher, it's usually awkward and embarrassing to be involved in their student's personal lives. Many students don't even think of them as actual individuals.\n\nTeacher/Parent Romance occurs when a teacher courts, or at least falls for, the parent of one of their students. In some areas and time-periods, it's against the law, or at least is socially unacceptable to do so, leading to either a Secret Relationship or waiting until the child is no longer the teacher's student.\n\nCompare and contrast to Teacher/Student Romance, which is when a teacher outright dates their student and is thus more of an Unequal Pairing. When the parent's new relationship is with a privately-hired tutor instead of a teacher, Marry the Nanny may be a closer fit. Related to Hot Teacher.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TeacherParentRomance", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ThePrincessDiaries", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/SweetGuiltyLoveBites", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/UQHolder", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MahouSenseiNegima", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/Frozen", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/LesChoristes", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/PayItForward", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/AllesIsLiefde", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Gifted", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/ChrisEvans", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ThePrincessDiaries", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheSantaClause", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Animorphs", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ThePrincessDiaries", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/PercyJacksonAndTheOlympians", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/FullHouse", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheAndyGriffithS